### DSL Program Example

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

### Execution Explanation

The DSL program defines a `SmartRoom` system. When run, each macro builds metamodel structs:

1. `system "SmartRoom" do...end` creates an `IoTSystem` struct, evaluates the block, and returns the populated struct.
2. `broker`, `node`, `topic` calls add their corresponding structs to the system.
3. `sensor :temp_sensor do...end` sets a Context Variable pointing to a new `Sensor` struct. The `trigger` and `publish` calls inside the block add `Trigger`, `SimpleCondition`, and `PublishAction` structs to that sensor. When `end` is reached, the sensor is finalized and added to the system.
4. `actuator :cooling_fan do...end` builds an `Actuator` with `ActuatorAction` entries, one per `on_message` call.
5. `coordinator :room_safety do...end` builds a `Coordinator` with a `Rule` containing a `CompoundCondition` (AND of two topic checks).

The `Printer` then traverses this struct tree and displays every component. The Data Flow section computes message routing by matching sensor publish topics to actuator/coordinator subscriptions, proving the metamodel was correctly instantiated.

```elixir
# DSL Program — Multi-Sensor Safety Alert
import IoTDSL

result = system "SmartRoom" do
  broker "192.168.1.100", port: 1883

  node :pi4, ip: "192.168.1.10"
  node :pi5, ip: "192.168.1.11"

  topic "temperature/high",    qos: :at_least_once
  topic "temperature/normal",  qos: :at_least_once
  topic "distance/close",      qos: :at_most_once
  topic "alerts/warning",      qos: :at_least_once

  sensor :temp_sensor, type: :temperature, gpio_pin: 4,
         sample_rate: {5, :seconds}, deployed_on: :pi4 do
    trigger :high_temp do
      condition :value, :greater_than, 30
      publish "temperature/high"
    end
    trigger :normal_temp do
      condition :value, :less_than, 20
      publish "temperature/normal"
    end
  end

  sensor :distance_sensor, type: :distance, gpio_pin: 27,
         sample_rate: {2, :seconds}, deployed_on: :pi4 do
    trigger :too_close do
      condition :value, :less_than, 20
      publish "distance/close"
    end
  end

  actuator :cooling_fan, type: :relay, gpio_pin: 24, deployed_on: :pi5 do
    on_message "temperature/high",   turn: :on
    on_message "temperature/normal", turn: :off
  end

  actuator :buzzer, type: :buzzer, gpio_pin: 23, deployed_on: :pi5 do
    on_message "alerts/warning", turn: :on, for: {3, :seconds}
  end

  coordinator :room_safety, deployed_on: :pi5,
              subscribes_to: ["temperature/high", "distance/close"] do
    rule :heat_and_close do
      compound_condition :and, ["temperature/high", "distance/close"]
      publish "alerts/warning", message: "High temp + object nearby"
    end
  end
end

IoTDSL.Printer.print(result)
```

### DSL's  Output

```
== IoT System: SmartRoom ============================
   Broker: 192.168.1.100:1883

-- Nodes -----------------------------------------------
  pi4 (192.168.1.10)
  pi5 (192.168.1.11)

-- Topics ----------------------------------------------
  "temperature/high" [QoS: 1 (at least once)]
  "temperature/normal" [QoS: 1 (at least once)]
  "distance/close" [QoS: 0 (at most once)]
  "alerts/warning" [QoS: 1 (at least once)]

-- Sensors ---------------------------------------------
  [temp_sensor]
    Type: temperature | GPIO: 4 | Rate: 5 seconds
    Deployed on: pi4
    Publishes to: temperature/normal, temperature/high
    Trigger: high_temp
      Condition: value > 30
      Action: publish -> "temperature/high"
    Trigger: normal_temp
      Condition: value < 20
      Action: publish -> "temperature/normal"
  [distance_sensor]
    Type: distance | GPIO: 27 | Rate: 2 seconds
    Deployed on: pi4
    Publishes to: distance/close
    Trigger: too_close
      Condition: value < 20
      Action: publish -> "distance/close"

-- Actuators -------------------------------------------
  [cooling_fan]
    Type: relay | GPIO: 24
    Deployed on: pi5
    Subscribes to: temperature/normal, temperature/high
    on "temperature/high" -> turn ON
    on "temperature/normal" -> turn OFF
  [buzzer]
    Type: buzzer | GPIO: 23
    Deployed on: pi5
    Subscribes to: alerts/warning
    on "alerts/warning" -> turn ON for 3 seconds

-- Coordinators ----------------------------------------
  [room_safety]
    Deployed on: pi5
    Subscribes to: temperature/high, distance/close
    Publishes to: alerts/warning
    Rule: heat_and_close
      Condition: topic == "temperature/high" AND topic == "distance/close"
      Action: publish -> "alerts/warning" (High temp + object nearby)

-- Data Flow -------------------------------------------
  temp_sensor --> "temperature/high" --> cooling_fan, room_safety
  temp_sensor --> "temperature/normal" --> cooling_fan
  distance_sensor --> "distance/close" --> room_safety
  room_safety --> "alerts/warning" --> buzzer

```
